The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 December is 11,197 (1,296 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 December, there were 976 new confirmed cases (113.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 December, there were 540 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 81% (436 extra cases).
